  "_doc": {
    "purpose": "Machine-readable feature/label window spec for the Layer-1 directional bias model (HYP-064). The single source of truth that tests/test_feature_label_isolation.py validates and docs/layer1/features.md describes in prose. Phase 1 only: this declares windows; no feature is computed and no model is trained.",
    "convention": "All offsets are in TRADING DAYS relative to the decision day t0 (0 = t0 close). A feature's computation_window = [earliest_offset, latest_offset], both <= 0 (a feature may NEVER use data after t0). The label is the sign of the forward return over the next N days = window [+1, +N].",
    "isolation_invariant": "For EVERY feature, computation_window.latest_offset < label.window.earliest_offset. Equivalently: every feature's data ends strictly before the label's forward window begins. This is the automated fix for the Sovereign Core / bias_engine.py tautology (label derived from a same-bar feature).",
    "calendar_note": "Calendar features (days_to_fomc, days_to_nfp) use PUBLICLY PRE-ANNOUNCED event dates known at t0 — that is not future market data and does not violate isolation. Their window is [0,0].",
    "hurst_exclusion": "Hurst is deliberately NOT a feature here — it was the label-derivation basis that made Sovereign Core ML a tautology (data/research/sovereign_core_verdict.md, Finding 3). It may only be used as a downstream regime gate, never as a model input."
  },
